articles.description: Four-star quarterback Jaden O'Neal, ranked No. 112 in the 2026 ESPN 300, announced his commitment to Florida State on Sunday night, sealing a long-anticipated flip for the former Oklahoma pledge.

articles.headline: Defensive end Richard Wesley commits to Texas Longhorns
articles.description: Defensive end Richard Wesley, a 6-foot-5, 250-pound pass rusher from Chatsworth, California, has committed to Texas, the No. 18 overall prospect in the 2026 ESPN 300 announced on Sunday night following an official visit with the Longhorns this weekend.

articles.headline: Ex-Buckeye Kirk Barton facing charge after fatal crash in Ohio
articles.description: Kirk Barton, a former captain at Ohio State who went on to play in the NFL, faces an aggravated vehicular manslaughter charge following a fatal crash early Saturday morning.

articles.headline: Notre Dame lands commitments from Khary Adams, Joey O'Brien
articles.description: Notre Dame landed pledges from a pair of top 2026 defensive back targets Friday, edging a trio of recruiting rivals to the commitments of No. 8 cornerback Khary Adams and No. 4 athlete prospect Joey O'Brien.

article.description: — Carter Bradley threw four touchdown passes — two of them to Devin Voisin — and South Alabama rolled to a 38-21 victory over Texas State on Saturday.

tracking.trackingName: NCF_One-Play (Carter Bradley throws 41-yard TD vs. Texas State) 2022/11/12 ESHEET

article.story: MOBILE, Ala. -- — Carter Bradley threw four touchdown passes — two of them to Devin Voisin — and South Alabama rolled to a 38-21 victory over Texas State on Saturday. Bradley hooked up with Voisin for a 41-yard touchdown on the first possession for South Alabama (8-2, 5-1 Sun Belt Conference) and Diego Guajardo kicked a 35-yard field goal to put the Jaguars up 10-0 after one quarter. Bradley hit DJ Thomas-Jones for a 2-yard touchdown in the second quarter and a 17-0 lead at halftime. Layne Hatcher got Texas State (3-7, 1-5) on the scoreboard midway through the third quarter on a 4-yard scoring toss to Rontavius Groves, but Bradley answered with a 41-yard scoring strike to Caullin Lacy and the Jaguars led 24-7 with one quarter to go. Bradley and Voisin teamed up for a 28-yard touchdown in the fourth quarter and Ke'Shun Brown capped the scoring with a 15-yard pick-6. Bradley completed 20 of 34 passes for 274 yards for South Alabama. Voisin hauled in six passes for 118 yards. Hatcher completed 24 of 42 passes for 143 yards for the Bobcats. ------
